    <h2>Directions &amp; public transport</h2>
    <p class="lead" style="max-width: 44rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
      Directions from Brandenburg Berlin Airport (BER) to the Hertie School (Mitte area).
    </p>

    <article class="card" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">
      <h3>Route 1 — Through Berlin Central Station (Hauptbahnhof)</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>BER to Berlin Central Station.</strong>
        The airport railway station is located directly below Terminal 1 on level U2. The Airport
        Express (FEX) runs several times an hour between "Flughafen BER — Terminal 1–2" and Berlin
        Central Station (Hauptbahnhof). The journey takes 30 minutes.
        More information on transportation from BER is available on the
        <a href="https://www.berlin-airport.de/en/travel/access-and-parking/by-public-transport/index.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BER airport site</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hauptbahnhof to the Hertie School.</strong>
        Take the U5 U-Bahn from Hauptbahnhof towards Hönow and exit at Unter den Linden.
        Head west on Unter den Linden toward Friedrichstraße (52 m), turn left onto Friedrichstraße
        (450 m), and the destination will be on the right.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Route 2 — Through Berlin Friedrichstraße Station</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>BER to Berlin Friedrichstraße Station.</strong>
        The regional trains (RE7, RB14) run several times an hour between "Flughafen BER —
        Terminal 1–2" and Berlin Friedrichstraße Station. The journey takes 30 minutes.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Friedrichstraße to the Hertie School.</strong>
        Take the U6 U-Bahn from Friedrichstraße towards Alt-Mariendorf and exit at Stadtmitte.
        Head east on Mohrenstrasse towards Friedrichstrasse (37 m), turn left onto Friedrichstraße
        (82 m), and the destination will be on the left.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

